WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:08.050
<i>It seems today that all you see</i>
<i>is violence in movies and sex on TV</i>

00:08.133 --> 00:11.720
<i>But where are those</i>
<i>Good old-fashioned values</i>

00:11.803 --> 00:14.389
<i>On which we used to rely?</i>

00:14.848 --> 00:18.060
<i>Lucky there's a family guy</i>

00:18.185 --> 00:21.563
<i>Lucky there's a man who</i>
<i>positively can do</i>

00:21.813 --> 00:23.148
<i>All the things that make us</i>

00:23.232 --> 00:24.608
<i>Laugh and cry!</i>

00:25.025 --> 00:29.988
<i>He's a family guy!</i>

00:34.993 --> 00:36.703
Hey, great idea bringing
the couch out here

00:36.787 --> 00:38.413
- from your den, Peter.
- Yeah, Lois and I

00:38.497 --> 00:40.666
dragged it out here last night
for a little hump sesh,

00:40.749 --> 00:42.209
so I figured I'd let it dry.

00:42.543 --> 00:44.962
"Couch." That's one of those words

00:45.045 --> 00:46.171
that if you say it over and over

00:46.255 --> 00:47.756
it starts to sound silly.

00:47.840 --> 00:49.967
Joe, you need
to take a class on small talk.

00:50.050 --> 00:52.177
You're not gonna believe this...
I'm in one.

00:52.511 --> 00:54.596
It sure is cloudy today.

00:54.721 --> 00:57.516
Good. You could have
also responded to Janet,

00:57.599 --> 00:59.059
who said her son died.

00:59.268 --> 01:02.521
I'm sorry your son died
on such a cloudy day.

01:08.193 --> 01:10.070
All right, kids, here's your bacon.

01:10.153 --> 01:12.322
- I call the paper towel!
- Aw, damn it!

01:12.489 --> 01:15.993
Ha-ha! You got to move fast
when Meg's at the table, Brian.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.203
All right, well, I get the box
when we have pizza for dinner.

01:18.370 --> 01:20.247
Uh-uh.
It doesn't work that way.

01:20.330 --> 01:22.207
You got to call it when it's happening.

01:22.374 --> 01:24.334
Good morning, family.
I'll be out front

01:24.418 --> 01:25.836
with the guys if anybody needs me.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.171
Peter, I thought we were gonna try

01:27.254 --> 01:29.047
to get the garden going again today.

01:29.298 --> 01:32.718
I know, sweetie, but then
I realized how stupid that is.

01:32.801 --> 01:35.304
Okay, bye. You guys are my everything.

01:35.596 --> 01:37.014
Why'd you ever marry him?

01:37.139 --> 01:40.392
Believe it or not, he used
to look like a young Gene Hackman.

01:40.684 --> 01:43.395
That's... that's not even good.

01:43.562 --> 01:44.605
It's gone!

01:44.771 --> 01:45.981
What? What's gone?

01:46.190 --> 01:48.525
Our drinking couch!
Somebody must've stole it!

01:48.734 --> 01:50.485
You left a couch out on the curb?

01:50.569 --> 01:52.571
Well, somebody probably thought
it was trash and took it.

01:52.779 --> 01:55.282
You said you were gonna bring
the couch right back in!

01:55.365 --> 01:57.951
- What were you thinking?
- I'll tell you what I was thinking.

01:58.035 --> 02:00.078
I was thinking we lived
in a safe neighborhood.

02:00.162 --> 02:01.413
But apparently, I was wrong!

02:01.580 --> 02:04.499
Wait, you're saying
you were wr... wr...

02:04.583 --> 02:07.127
wro... wrrr...

02:07.211 --> 02:09.838
Oh, I get it...
the Fonz can't say "wrong."

02:09.922 --> 02:12.633
No, Peter, he's 70...
he's having a stroke.

02:17.888 --> 02:19.848
Wow, Peter, I think
starting a community watch

02:19.932 --> 02:22.976
- is a great idea.
- Yeah, I even got shirts made up for us.

02:23.268 --> 02:24.603
This is quality work.

02:24.686 --> 02:26.772
Where did you get these?
Via the Web?

02:26.855 --> 02:28.232
Hey, listen, Joe,

02:28.315 --> 02:29.858
you think you can get us all guns?

02:30.108 --> 02:31.693
No, Peter, they're too dangerous.

02:31.777 --> 02:33.779
Besides, you can't just go get a gun,

02:33.862 --> 02:36.031
you have to be certified in gun safety,

02:36.114 --> 02:38.367
go through an extensive
background screening process.

02:38.492 --> 02:39.868
- Got 'em.
- Whoa.

02:39.993 --> 02:41.036
How'd you get 'em so quick?

02:41.119 --> 02:43.330
It was easy...
like pressing that "easy" button

02:43.413 --> 02:44.998
at the office supply store.

02:45.123 --> 02:46.959
- Hey, thanks for all your help.
- No problem.

02:47.042 --> 02:48.836
Why don't you go ahead
and hit the "easy" button.

02:48.919 --> 02:49.920
Okay.

02:50.921 --> 02:53.632
What did I just do?
Don't worry about it.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.430
Hey, Quagmire, you're a sex guy.

03:00.514 --> 03:03.559
You watch any good pornos lately?

03:03.642 --> 03:06.103
I mean... I guess.

03:06.186 --> 03:07.521
So what's your pleasure?

03:07.604 --> 03:09.022
What kind of movies you like?

03:09.106 --> 03:11.650
I don't know.
MILF stuff's kind of cool.

03:11.733 --> 03:13.151
What... what about you?

03:13.235 --> 03:15.988
Me? I have very particular tastes.

03:16.071 --> 03:18.198
- I like a soapy bottom.
- What?

03:18.282 --> 03:19.867
Soft-core soaped-up butts,

03:19.950 --> 03:21.994
like from a PG-13 camp movie.

03:22.077 --> 03:24.580
I can't get enough of it.
Drives me wild.

03:24.663 --> 03:26.206
Okay, let's talk
about something else.

03:26.290 --> 03:27.541
All right...

03:29.168 --> 03:31.587
it's kind of too cool
for the air-conditioner

03:31.670 --> 03:33.380
and too warm for the heater, huh?

03:34.715 --> 03:37.384
Ah, got to walk that boner off, huh?

03:37.467 --> 03:38.844
Yeah.

03:42.264 --> 03:44.057
Hey, guys, you better come with me.

03:44.141 --> 03:46.643
There's some weird, big-nose guy
hiding in the bushes

03:46.727 --> 03:48.187
