14:02.217 --> 14:05.470
How is it that I'm only
just now meeting you?

14:07.848 --> 14:09.474
Look, Carter, you got to believe me.

14:09.558 --> 14:11.935
I didn't shoot Cleveland Jr.
because he was black!

14:12.144 --> 14:14.021
Hey, you don't have
to tell me that.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.690
But the media's out there
making you look like a monster,

14:16.773 --> 14:19.443
all for exercising
your constitutional rights.

14:19.610 --> 14:20.777
Grover's a monster.

14:20.944 --> 14:23.071
But don't worry.
We're gonna get you out of this.

14:23.155 --> 14:24.740
I'll be damned if I'm gonna sit back

14:24.823 --> 14:26.533
and let them do this
to one of my own.

14:26.658 --> 14:28.619
- What, you mean your family?
- Huh?

14:28.744 --> 14:30.245
Oh, yeah, yeah, that. Yeah, right.

14:30.454 --> 14:32.080
Look, I'm gonna bail you out of here,

14:32.164 --> 14:34.583
set you up with my lawyer,
and get these charges dropped.

14:34.750 --> 14:35.834
Well, how you gonna do that?

14:36.084 --> 14:37.753
Don't worry.
I'll come up with a good story,

14:37.836 --> 14:39.129
and they'll eat it up.

14:39.213 --> 14:41.507
Not like when I read
my JAG fan fiction

14:41.590 --> 14:43.634
at the NCIS convention.

14:43.800 --> 14:45.344
"JAG stood up and yelled,

14:45.427 --> 14:47.971
"'Objection, Your Honor, by Navy law.

14:48.055 --> 14:49.723
"He then turned to the lady lawyer,

14:49.806 --> 14:51.600
"the gal from the October <i>Maxim,</i>

14:51.683 --> 14:53.018
"who still managed to be hot

14:53.101 --> 14:55.896
"despite her sexless, pageboy haircut.

14:55.979 --> 14:57.356
"Or perhaps because of it."

14:57.439 --> 14:58.732
- Boo!
- Terrible!

14:58.857 --> 15:01.860
Right branch of the military,
wrong investigative arm!

15:07.616 --> 15:09.993
And I was trying to
get back into my house,

15:10.077 --> 15:12.871
and my neighbor, Mr. Griffin, shot me.

15:13.121 --> 15:15.082
He said he felt threatened by me,

15:15.165 --> 15:17.501
and that hurt even worse
than getting shot!

15:17.668 --> 15:19.086
Aw!

15:19.294 --> 15:21.755
Your Honor, permission
to hug the witness?

15:21.839 --> 15:22.840
Granted.

15:25.259 --> 15:26.760
Don't worry, Mr. Griffin.

15:26.844 --> 15:27.928
You're every bit as sympathetic

15:28.011 --> 15:29.972
as this chubby-cheeked cocoa angel.

15:30.055 --> 15:32.015
I haven't been listening.
What's goin' on?

15:32.266 --> 15:33.809
I don't think it's lost on any of us

15:33.892 --> 15:36.103
that the laws are written on white paper.

15:36.186 --> 15:38.564
Yeah, white paper.
Check your jacket pocket.

15:38.814 --> 15:40.399
"I don't think it's lost on any of us

15:40.482 --> 15:42.234
"that the laws
are written on white paper."

15:42.317 --> 15:43.819
Hey, look, I'm just saying,

15:43.902 --> 15:46.530
it's no surprise
that justice isn't colorblind.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.031
Check your other jacket pocket.

15:48.490 --> 15:49.658
"Hey, look, I'm just saying

15:49.741 --> 15:51.702
"it's no surprise
that justice isn't colorblind."

15:51.785 --> 15:52.828
Stewie, you're a jerk!

15:52.911 --> 15:54.037
Check Chris' pocket.

15:54.413 --> 15:55.873
What? There's nothing in here, and...

15:55.956 --> 15:58.250
Oh, God, the bottom of the pocket's
been cut out!

15:58.417 --> 15:59.668
Thanks, Brian!

15:59.751 --> 16:02.838
I was the mastermind
behind this whole thing!

16:03.046 --> 16:04.173
Your witness.

16:04.965 --> 16:06.383
All right, watch this.

16:06.466 --> 16:09.344
This is where we take control
of the situation.

16:09.553 --> 16:12.347
Mr. Brown, you testified
that you were listening to music

16:12.431 --> 16:14.266
- at the time of the shooting.
- That's right.

16:14.433 --> 16:17.269
- And isn't Jay-Z music?
- Yes.

16:17.477 --> 16:21.023
And doesn't he have the lyrics,
"I put the gun to you.

16:21.106 --> 16:23.150
"I'll kill ya, I'll chop ya up,

16:23.233 --> 16:25.652
"put ya inside the mattress
like drug money"?

16:27.154 --> 16:30.490
I was listening
to Neil Sedaka's Hanukkah album.

16:30.657 --> 16:32.284
And isn't true
that your last name

16:32.367 --> 16:34.328
is the same as Chris Brown's?

16:34.411 --> 16:35.913
Yes, but I don't see what...

16:35.996 --> 16:37.915
And what did Chris Brown do to Rihanna?

16:38.081 --> 16:40.501
He hit her, like, a hundred times.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.586
Your Honor, I'd like
to enter into evidence

16:42.669 --> 16:44.922
this photo of a badly beaten Rihanna

16:45.005 --> 16:47.633
as well as this print ad
for the <i>Entourage</i> movie.

16:47.716 --> 16:48.717
Why?

16:48.800 --> 16:50.052
I can't unsee this!

16:50.135 --> 16:51.178
Who is this for?

16:51.303 --> 16:52.471
What's he doing?

16:52.554 --> 16:54.389
He's making Cleveland Jr.
look like a thug.

16:54.556 --> 16:56.225
I know. That's the idea.

16:56.308 --> 16:57.976
You don't want to go
back to jail, do you?

17:03.690 --> 17:04.733
I don't know.

17:05.400 --> 17:06.401
Maybe.

17:06.693 --> 17:09.238
Mr. Brown, please pick up this knife.

17:09.655 --> 17:10.822
Aah! He's got a knife!

17:21.625 --> 17:22.835
This isn't fair!

17:22.918 --> 17:25.462
They're making my son
look like a common hoodlum!

17:25.546 --> 17:27.756
Joe, you're a cop! Do something!

17:27.965 --> 17:29.967
No, the soap covers everything.

17:30.050 --> 17:33.178
You might see, like,
the very top of the crack,

17:33.262 --> 17:35.556
but that's... that's not what it's about.

17:40.310 --> 17:42.312
How do you sleep at night?

17:42.563 --> 17:44.982
Propped up on pillows,
on account of my fat throat.

17:45.065 --> 17:46.900
If I lay flat on my back, I die.

17:46.984 --> 17:49.653
I need pillows
between my thighs myself.

17:49.736 --> 17:51.780
And this friendship is over!

18:02.583 --> 18:04.084
Thanks for letting me sit in the back.

18:04.168 --> 18:05.752
I was flipping people off the whole way.

18:08.046 --> 18:10.007
Get out of here, all of you!

18:10.090 --> 18:12.926
My son didn't do anything wrong!

18:16.805 --> 18:19.933
Carter, I think this has
all kind of gone too far.

18:20.017 --> 18:21.018
What do you think you're doing?

18:21.101 --> 18:23.103
I'm gonna make this right.

18:24.563 --> 18:25.981
Everyone! Everyone!

18:26.231 --> 18:28.233
Listen, I have something to say.

18:28.317 --> 18:30.736
Cleveland Jr. doesn't deserve any of this.

18:30.819 --> 18:34.031
All those things you heard
about Cleveland Jr. were lies.

18:34.114 --> 18:35.449
He didn't do anything to me.

18:35.532 --> 18:38.076
He's a good kid, from a good family.

18:38.368 --> 18:41.121
I just got scared,
and I did something stupid.

18:41.205 --> 18:43.707
I swear, it had nothing to do
with the color of his skin,

18:43.790 --> 18:46.418
but... I did shoot him.

18:48.170 --> 18:51.173
I deserve to be held
responsible for my actions.

18:51.256 --> 18:53.634
Even if that means going to jail.

18:53.842 --> 18:55.177
You heard him, other cops.

18:55.260 --> 18:56.470
Let's take him in.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.555
He doesn't know our names, does he?

18:58.639 --> 18:59.765
I don't think he does.

19:03.685 --> 19:04.853
Wait a minute.

19:04.937 --> 19:06.605
Peter didn't shoot my son.

19:06.855 --> 19:08.148
I did.

19:09.525 --> 19:11.985
Peter was just taking the blame for me.

19:12.069 --> 19:13.737
He's a good friend.

19:14.238 --> 19:17.407
Mr. Brown, what exactly are you saying?

19:17.616 --> 19:21.036
I'm saying that I,
Cleveland Brown, a black man,

19:21.119 --> 19:23.413
shot Cleveland Brown, Jr.,

19:23.497 --> 19:24.915
another black man.

19:28.168 --> 19:29.962
Wait, where did everybody go?

19:30.045 --> 19:31.880
You want to make the media go away?

19:31.964 --> 19:34.216
Just mention black-on-black crime.

19:34.424 --> 19:36.635
Boy, the world we live in, huh?

19:36.718 --> 19:39.096
Brian, reach into Meg's pocket.

19:39.179 --> 19:40.722
Go ahead, Brian.

19:40.889 --> 19:42.891
I... I don't want to.

19:43.141 --> 19:45.269
Cleveland, why did you do that?

19:45.352 --> 19:49.273
Peter, since this is about racism,
why don't we take a slow,

19:49.356 --> 19:52.150
hands-clasped-behind-
the-back walk together?

19:52.234 --> 19:55.195
Listen, I know you wouldn't
have shot Cleveland Jr.

19:55.279 --> 19:56.572
on account of his race.

19:56.655 --> 19:58.699
You shot him because you're stupid.

19:58.782 --> 20:00.659
That's all I'm trying to say!

20:00.868 --> 20:03.203
And I know you don't have
hate in your heart.

20:03.287 --> 20:06.164
You were willing to go to jail
for shooting my son.

20:06.248 --> 20:08.166
You took responsibility.

20:08.250 --> 20:09.877
That's what's important.

20:10.085 --> 20:12.212
So... you forgive me?

20:12.504 --> 20:14.339
Of course I do.

20:14.715 --> 20:17.050
Oh, thanks, Cleveland.

20:18.093 --> 20:19.761
Hey, how you feeling there, champ?

20:19.845 --> 20:20.846
I'm good.

20:20.929 --> 20:22.097
Getting better every day.

20:22.181 --> 20:23.640
Aw, I'm happy to hear that.

20:23.932 --> 20:26.768
Look, I hope you know I'm sorry.

20:26.935 --> 20:28.687
Hey, these things happen.

20:28.937 --> 20:30.480
That's my boy.

20:32.983 --> 20:34.610
- Mr. Griffin?
- Yeah?

20:34.693 --> 20:35.944
Just so you know,

20:36.028 --> 20:37.779
I'm gonna be coming for your ass.

20:37.863 --> 20:39.156
Wh... What's that now?

20:39.364 --> 20:40.824
I'm saying it's on!

20:40.908 --> 20:42.910
You ever feel the cool steel

20:42.993 --> 20:45.662
of a switchblade
pressed against your temple?

20:47.206 --> 20:48.999
Hey, Mr. Griffin,

20:49.124 --> 20:50.250
I'm just kidding.

20:50.417 --> 20:51.585
Or am I?

20:51.668 --> 20:54.171
You're gonna wonder about that,
you fat bitch.

20:54.254 --> 20:55.255
See you later!
